This paper deals with natural language generation, specifically the task of imitating input text. It proposes two algorithms for generating philosophical statements, one using interpolated Markov models and the other using dynamic templates. These algorithms are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
